## Project Rules
Conventions specific to this codebase.

- All Rhai API functions are registered in src/api/ — one file per API domain (fs, shell, env, http)
- main.rs only wires modules and launches the engine — no business logic
- Compile-time constants live in src/state/ (sizes, durations, limits, paths, urls)
- Error types defined per module — never inline errors at call sites
- `anyhow` is allowed ONLY in main.rs (CLI boundary) — all other code uses thiserror enums
- Rhai API functions return Dynamic or Result<Dynamic, Box<EvalAltResult>> — match Rhai's type system
- No `println!` — use `tracing::{info, warn, error}` except for explicit script output (print/eprint builtins)

